<div class="info-box">
  <h3><i class="fas fa-stream"></i> Types of XSS Covered</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Stored XSS (Persistent):</strong> Malicious scripts originate from
      the website's own database.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Reflected XSS (Non-Persistent):</strong> Malicious scripts
      originate from the victim's request.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>DOM-Based XSS:</strong> The vulnerability exists in the
      client-side code rather than server-side code.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    For each type, you'll find examples of vulnerable implementations and how
    they can be secured.
  </p>
</div>

